article.headline: Delaware 70, Boston U. 68
article.story: BOSTON -- D.J. Boney drained a 3-pointer from the left corner with 4.1 seconds remaining, capping career-high 14 points and sealing Delaware' 70-68 win over Boston University on Sunday. Jawan Carter added 16 points and 9 assists to help Delaware stave off the Terriers, who had rallied from eight points down in the final 3:44 to take a 68-67 lead on two free throws by Matt Wolff with 12.5 seconds left. With BU out of timeouts, Corey Lowe raced into the frontcourt, but was stripped by Carter as time expired. Lowe led the Terriers with 20 points and six rebounds. Alphonso Dawson led the Blue Hens with 20 points as Delaware (5-6) bagged its third straight win. Wolff had 10 points and 12 rebounds for the first double-double of his career and the team's first of the season as Boston University (5-5) lost two straight games for the first time this season.
